OL,3,CAnalysis: Autumn tax rises loom as
OL,4,Cgovernment borrowing rises in June
OL,6,FThe economic outlook for autumn looks
OL,7,Fbleak and tax rises likely, as ITV
OL,8,FNews Economics Editor Joel Hills
OL,9,Fexplains.
OL,11,FThe government borrowed #20.7 billion
OL,12,Fin June - #6.6 billion more than the
OL,13,Fsame month last year, and far above
OL,14,Fthe #16.5 billion City economists had
OL,15,Fforecast.
OL,17,FIn fact, it was the second highest
OL,18,FJune borrowing figure on record,
OL,19,Faccording to the Office for National
OL,20,FStatistics, which began tracking
OL,21,Fmonthly borrowing in 1993.
