OL,3,CAnalysis: Autumn tax rises loom as
OL,4,Cgovernment borrowing rises in June
OL,6,FOn the face of it, the detail is as
OL,7,Ftroubling as the headline number.
OL,9,FJune's numbers look dreadful. But
OL,10,Fdespite the overshoot, borrowing for
OL,11,Fthe first quarter of the financial
OL,12,Fyear (April`June) is more or less bang
OL,13,Fin line with the OBR's forecast.
OL,15,FEven so, the outlook for autumn is
OL,16,Fdark.
